column2: Has been windy for several days.  Sunny today and windy.
Some mud like bodies floating in shallows.  Some green slime hanging in the shallows.
Lots of green slime in shallows.
Aquatic plant growth now breaking the surface in many areas.
After 3 days of rain- lots of wind.  Hard to believe so clear.  Lots of green muck in shallows.
Water level up 6 inches.  Heavy rain 2 days ago.
Some green stuff on water surface
Nice day - much rain previous week.
Two days after heavy rain.  Lots of surface algae (scum) on shores.
Lots of surface green scum - water green.
More weeds than in 3 years.  More surface algae.
Gave up trying to keep weeds away from dock.
strong wind most of night- april 16th- next morning

column1: all ice gone ice out 4/16

column2: green scum near shore noticeable already
nice sunny day.  Low humidity.  Lots of scum near shore.
Lots of weeds for this early
very hot and muggy for the past week.  Clear- sunny- hot again today.  2/3 inch of rain last night.
Very hot- muggy days for the past week.  So many weeds in our bay; green scum floating on the water.
Very hot- muggy- clear day.  Lots of scum and weed growth within 100 feet of shoreline.
We've had a lot of rain lately.  Excess weeds in bays; some green scum on surface of water.
Hot- muggy weather continues.  Today overcast- light sprinkles.  Excess weeds in bay.
Rain + Winds Previous Eve.  Lots of weeds.  Alk Level 112 ppm.
3 1/2 inches of rain on Aug 2. Windy out of South; water stirred up. Scuba'd today with very poor visibility.
It has been rainy and cold.   Lots of green algae in

column1: the water but not a whole lot accumulating along the shore on top of the
water.   Weeds are better and have died down a great deal.

column2: Water is Murky.. Expected to find it clearer  Think Turnover has begun... (Another observer found water temperatures weren't the same at all depths till Oct 18- so turnover wasn't complete at this time)
Cold-rainy-snow nite before;  weeds have subsided;

column1: turnover looks like it has just begun.   Freeze over of the lake was early this year on November 26

column2: Pulled our boat out for the end of the season.
Ice out was 8 days ago on April 14- after a day and

column1: night of windy conditions.

column2: Curly leaf pond weed is the worst we have seen in 4

column1: years.   It seems to be choking out everything.  We have had a spell of
cold weather which may have turned off the Bluegill spawning- but their
beds are so inundated with pond weed that am wondering if that isn't
causing a problem for the fish spawn.   The lake has already stratified
and there is almost no oxygen below 30 feet.   Have been advised that will
probably mean massive algae blooms in the weeks ahead.... this is being
submitted much later than the test.... which has come true..

column2: This is Monday and is cloudy and overcast with light

column1: wind.   Has been a beautiful weekend with no rain since Friday.   Lots of
Algae accumulating in the shallows weeds are tolerable.   Crinkle Leaf
pond weed is abating... the pond weed was the worst I have seen it in 4
years this spring.

column2: Lots of algae hanging in the water making it very

column1: cloudy....  There has been a drought for most of the month of August and
no rain yet in Sept..   The weeds have pretty much subsided making fishing
off the dock easier and less stuff to tangle motor pr

column2: Craig Roesler and Dave Blumer used Harold Blumer's boat to test new YSI meters (63 + 55) on this lake
Secchi readings were not taken- as we do not have a Secchi disk.  My son Logan was also with us.
